@jreback : what are your thoughts on the testing approach in the new file I just pushed, `test_interval_specific.py`? Haven't made any changes other than adding this file; didn't want to do too much in case I'm heading down the wrong path.

The idea is to use this approach to test behavior that depends on the underlying structure of the intervals in the index (e.g. overlapping vs. nonoverlapping monotonic), such as `get_loc`, which has specific code paths for different scenarios like this.  Behavior that is independent from the underlying interval structure (e.g. `IntervalIndex.mid`) can be left in the existing `test_interval.py` setting.

Was a little complicated to get all of this set up, but shouldn't be too bad now if someone else wanted to create a new test class variation, e.g. `TestMonotonicDecreasing`.  Not at all tied to the name `test_interval_specific.py` either; could even see this being split off into separate files for each child class, e.g. `test_interval_overlapping.py`.
